@Override
protected void doPost(HttpServletRequest req, HttpServletResponse resp) throws ServletException, IOException {
    String vName = req.getParameter("username");
    String vPass = req.getParameter("password");
    String rememberMe = req.getParameter("rememberMe");
    PrintWriter out = resp.getWriter();

    resp.setContentType("text/html");

    // Get saved cookies
    String savedUsername = getCookieValue(req, "username");
    String savedPassword = getCookieValue(req, "password");
    String savedGender = getCookieValue(req, "gender");
    String savedEmail = getCookieValue(req, "email");
    String savedPhoneNumber = getCookieValue(req, "phoneNum");

    // Check if login credentials match the saved cookies
    if (vName != null && vPass != null && vName.equals(savedUsername) && vPass.equals(savedPassword)) {
        // If "rememberMe" is checked, save user data to cookies with a long expiration time
        if ("on".equals(rememberMe)) {
            int longExpiry = 60 * 60 * 24; // 24 hours
            createCookie(resp, "username", vName, longExpiry);
            createCookie(resp, "password", vPass, longExpiry);
            createCookie(resp, "gender", savedGender, longExpiry);
            createCookie(resp, "email", savedEmail, longExpiry);
            createCookie(resp, "phoneNum", savedPhoneNumber, longExpiry);
        }

        printWelcome(vName, vPass, savedGender, savedEmail, savedPhoneNumber, out);
    } else {
        // Display error message and redirect to the login page or display a login form
        out.println("<h2 style='color:red'>Invalid login credentials!</h2>");
        out.println("<a href='login'>Go back to login</a>");
    }

    out.println("</body></html>");
}
```

With these changes, cookies will be created with a short expiration time during registration to store user data temporarily. When the user logs in, the `Welcome` servlet will validate the credentials and store them in cookies with a long expiration time if the "rememberMe" option is checked. The user will be able to access the `Welcome` page directly if the "rememberMe" option was checked during login.

